        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 7:20PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 720 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Lelia Lake, or 12 miles southeast of Clarendon, moving
north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hedley and Lelia Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
